Bill,

I need to bring to your attention a serious safety incident that occurred
yesterday at the Baytown welding facility.

At approximately 2:15 PM, a flash fire broke out in Welding Bay 3 during
a routine pipe fitting operation. Two workers sustained minor burns and
were transported to Memorial Hermann for evaluation.

Preliminary investigation suggests:
- The fire suppression system in Bay 3 was last inspected 18 months ago
  (should be every 6 months per OSHA 1910.252)
- The welding curtains were not properly positioned
- One worker was not wearing required PPE (face shield)

I've already contacted our insurance carrier and OSHA regional office.
We need to schedule an emergency safety review ASAP.

Francis Ham
Plant Manager, Baytown Operations

